org.eclipse.dataset

Class SummedAreaTable

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.dataset.SummedAreaTable

  • public class SummedAreaTable
extends java.lang.Object
    This code is based on: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Summed_area_table This class can calculate the sum of a box region very fast compared to ROIProfile. Therefore for instance if calculating means of ROIs within a given plot, create a SummedAreaTable and do the calculation through that. I(x,y) = i(x,y) + I(x-1,y) + I(x,y-1) - I(x-1,y-1) getDouble(...) and set(Object, ...) On Dataset are slow. Therefore we have replaced these with absolute index.
    Author:
    Matthew Gerring

        public Dataset getFanoImage(int... box)
                     throws java.lang.Exception
        Creates a fano image where each pixel is the fano factor for a give box surrounding it. This operation has improved speed because it uses the summed area table to compute a fast mean and variance for a given box.

      • getBoxVariance

        public double getBoxVariance(IRectangularROI box)
                      throws java.lang.Exception
        Get the variance for a given box. (1/n)(S2 - S1^2/n) Where: S1 is sum of box ( D+A-B-C of sum ) S2 is sum^2 of box ( D+A-B-C of sum ) n is number of pixels box covers
        Parameters:
